						<summary>

						<p>Pillar standing in front of a <hi rend="italic">liṅga</hi> in a field to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>This undated record may be assigned to the 9th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It mentions Śrī Ṭhakura Satti Komāra and seems to refer to the construction of a stone temple at Aṇivūṟu.</p>						

						</summary>
